author: Discovery
description:
Josh Gates’ journey uncovers lost civilizations, beginning with the vanished settlers of Roanoke. He then examines John Franklin’s 1845 Northwest Passage expedition, whose crew ran out of food, ate polar bear meat that made them sick and turned to cannibalism. Gates also explores the underground tunnels of Teotihuacan, Mexico, and searches for hidden chambers in Petra. #ExpeditionUnknown

About Expedition Unknown: 
Josh Gates investigates the truth behind the world's most iconic and captivating legends. Leaving no stone unturned, his adventures take him around the globe as he immerses himself in the core locales linked to each tale.
